Another diversion attack by Azerbaijan - Panorama
On June 6, at about 4:15 am an Azerbaijani intelligence-diversion group attempted to enter NKR Defense Army’s posts in the southern region of contact line between Nagorno-Karabakh and Azerbaijan, in Horadiz direction.
NKR forces halted Azerbaijan’s attack, with considerable casualties sustained by Azerbaijan. Casualties are also reported on the Armenian side. As a result of Azeri sabotage, Jr. Sergeant Vardan Ohanyan was killed and soldiers Arayik Mavreyan and Volodya Tsatryan were injured, NKR Defense Army’s press service said.  